# Security Policy

## Reporting a Vulnerability

**Do not open a public issue for security vulnerabilities.**

Report privately to **[security contact — email or GitHub private advisory link]**.
Include:

- A description of the issue and its impact.
- Steps to reproduce (proof-of-concept if possible).
- Affected version(s) and environment.

You can expect an acknowledgment within **[timeframe, e.g. 48 hours]** and a
status update within **[timeframe, e.g. 5 business days]**.

## Disclosure Process

1. You report privately.
2. We confirm the issue and determine affected versions.
3. We develop and test a fix.
4. We release the fix and publish an advisory, crediting you unless you prefer
   to remain anonymous.

We ask that you give us **[e.g. 90 days]** to address the issue before any
public disclosure.

## Supported Versions

| Version | Supported |
|---------|-----------|
| [1.x]   | ✅ |
| [< 1.0] | ❌ |

